.TH DBX-TEST 1 "2026-06-20" "dbx 0.37.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dbx-test \- test connectivity to a configured host
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dbx test
.I host
.PP
.B dbx ping
.I host
.SH DESCRIPTION
Try to reach
.I host
using the configured connection parameters. For SSH-tunneled hosts,
opens the tunnel and runs a
.B SELECT 1
through the managed Docker client. Reports which step succeeded /
failed so you can localize a problem (DNS, SSH, DB auth).
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.nf
dbx test production
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Reached the database successfully.
.TP
non-zero
SSH tunnel failed, DB auth failed, or the host isn't in
.IR config.json .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dbx (1),
.BR dbx-host (1),
.BR dbx-query (1).
